<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading mw-first-heading">List of countries by past and projected GDP (nominal)</h1>

<div id="bodyContent" class="vector-body">

<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>

<div id="contentSub"></div>

<div id="contentSub2"></div>

<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>

<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>

<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#searchInput">Jump to search</a>

<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content mw-content-ltr" lang="en" dir="ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p class="mw-empty-elt">

 

</p><p>This is an alphabetical <b>list of countries by past and projected <a href="/wiki/Gross_domestic_product" title="Gross domestic product">gross domestic product</a> (nominal)</b> as ranked by the IMF. Figures are based on official <a href="/wiki/Exchange_rate" title="Exchange rate">exchange rates</a>, not on the <a href="/wiki/Purchasing_power_parity" title="Purchasing power parity">purchasing power parity</a> (PPP) methodology. Values are given in millions of <a href="/wiki/United_States_dollar" title="United States dollar">United States dollars</a> (USD) and have not been adjusted for inflation. These figures have been taken from the <a href="/wiki/International_Monetary_Fund" title="International Monetary Fund">International Monetary Fund</a>'s World Economic Outlook (WEO) Database (April 2022 edition) and/or other sources.<sup id="cite_ref-IMF_Data_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-IMF_Data-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>

</p><p>For older GDP trends, see <a href="/wiki/List_of_regions_by_past_GDP_(PPP)" title="List of regions by past GDP (PPP)">List of regions by past GDP (PPP)</a>.

</p>

<h2><span id="GDP_milestones_by_countries_.28in_trillions_USD.29"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="GDP_milestones_by_countries_(in_trillions_USD)">GDP milestones by countries (in trillions USD)</span></h2>
